    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="847"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24522/12–445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 4, 1945—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>841. I read to Minister Foreign Affairs this morning the Dept’s 702, Dec 3, 6
                    p.m., regarding Salinas Base. Minister expressed himself as being in complete
                    accord with all the points covered by Dept’s telegram.</p>
                <pb facs="1046" n="1032" xml:id="pg_1032"/>
                <p>He will make request that we leave a small number of technicians for training
                    purposes.</p>
                <p>He will also agree in an exchange of notes giving US transit rights et cetera. In
                    order to avoid any misunderstanding I would appreciate Dept’s telegraphing me a
                    clarification of “technical stop” as well as “reciprocal basis”, both of which
                    appear in point 3 of Deptel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
